What will Taapsee Pannu ( @taapsee ) wear on her wedding day? The Bride’s Today coverstar has a clear vision for the outfit of her dreams. “I really don’t want to get into that rat race of the biggest designers,” she shares. “I mean they have awesome work, I love their work, I wear them during my work events. But when it comes to something as close as my wedding, my best friend from college – Mani Bhatia – is the best option. I think that will be the perfect gift for her actually to give to me. I’m not going to pay for that,” she laughs. “But it will be something so personalised that it’ll go beyond in memories.”

#BTBeauty A Step-By Step Guide to Give Yourself an At-Home Facial 

Repeatedly wearing makeup, a change of weather and late nights out can take a toll on your skin during the wedding and festive season. Pamper your skin by following these DIY steps shared by celebrity dermatologist @dr.chytra

1) Cleanse: Use a Ph balanced, soap-free cleansers or micellar water.

2) Exfoliation: Use active exfoliants like glycolic acid, lactic acid, salicylic acid or gluconolactone. You can also use enzyme exfoliants like papaya and pumpkin. Do not use scrubs or beads on the face and neck.

3) Massage: Use shea butter, mango butter, cocoa butter or oil for dry skin.

4) Repair: Use hyaluronic acid serum, niacinamide serum, vitamin E serum or pigment lightening gels. 

5) Mask: Clay masks are ideal. Kaolin or fullers earth for oily skin, calamine mask for sensitive Skin and sheet mask for normal skin.

In a #BridesTodayExclusive, Sonakshi Sinha (@aslisona) says that the qualities that drew her to Zaheer Iqbal (@iamzahero) are the things she always wanted in a partner. “He is very generous and respectful, the qualities I wanted in my man. It’s hard to find someone open and expressive about their feelings in today’s world…

On the other hand, Iqbal reveals that the strength of their relationship lies in their shared groundedness, in how their core beliefs and desires are the same. “Our connection was evident from the day we met. It was our love for travel, more than anything, and that we are both really simple people. In spite of coming from privileged backgrounds, we share the same core beliefs and want the same thing in life—happiness. We’re not superficial people. She’s very relatable.
